f=Executive Office/vista/marketplace/rice-prioritization/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "rice-prioritization" skill, selected fulfill catalog's "rice-prioritization" slot vista RICE scoring roadmap items ranking, strategy sanity-check, re-scoring discipline. Chosen over mcorbett51090/RavenClaude candidate because skill's calibrate score sensitivity-check recommend flow runs autonomously produces saved, auditable report (consistent marcus's venture-priority-matrix), alternative framed around facilitating human prioritization meeting. TWO NOTES SYSTEM, flagged rather edited source: Stage dispatches one scorer subagent initiative parallel. runtime doesn't support subagents, degrade cleanly: score items one time shared framing calibrated definitions discipline calibration, parallelism. "When use" cross-references sibling skills source repo (weighted-decision-matrix, impact-feasibility-matrix, kano-model) copied here. Kept verbatim copy-without-cutting; treat them pointers source repo, local skills. Boundary marcus: venture-priority-matrix ranks VENTURES/initiatives competing resource pool (6-factor weighted score); skill sequences ROADMAP ITEMS/features within venture RICE. Different altitude, overlap. --> · h1:rice-prioritization=Ranks backlog RICE (Reach Impact Confidence) Effort, built Intercom settle backlog fights without loudest voice winning. input guess, items guessed definitions, ranking reflects relative value rather relative volume advocacy. formula, four factors, their scales, built-in Confidence bias check, sensitivity logic, pitfalls live [references/rice.md](references/rice.md). Load file before scoring. · h2:When to use=user many roadmap initiatives features differ reach, impact, effort, wants them sequenced expected value. RICE sequences backlog; pick among handful designs. Use [weighted-decision-matrix](../weighted-decision-matrix/SKILL.md) CHOOSE among options bespoke weighted criteria. Use [impact-feasibility-matrix](../impact-feasibility-matrix/SKILL.md) quick two-axis sort reach confidence don't matter enough model. Use [kano-model](../kano-model/SKILL.md) understand WHICH features matter why; Kano explains demand, RICE sequences supply. two three items, overhead calibration buys little: rank them hand. · h2:Language=Conduct session write report language user writing in. reference file English; keep framework keyed regardless output language. · h2:Inputs=**INITIATIVES** (required): backlog features initiatives rank. goal given without list, ask items first., **GOAL** (optional): metric Impact measured against (activation, revenue, retention). absent, fix user Stage without Impact referent., **CONTEXT** (optional): known data (usage figures, past effort actuals), planning horizon, any hard constraints commitments pre-empt ranking. · h2:Orchestration map=`Stage 1  Calibrate      ── fix goal, Reach window, Impact scale, Confidence levels, Effort unit WITH the user (inline) \· Stage 2  Score items    ── 1 scorer subagent per initiative IN PARALLEL ──┐  (estimate R, I, C, E with rationale) \· Stage 3  Synthesis      ── 1 agent, needs all items ────────────────────┘  (compute, rank, sensitivity, roadmap order)` · h2:Orchestration map=Tell subagent final message return value: structured data, prose human. Subagents use available retrieval tools ground estimates real evidence. · h2:Stage Calibrate (inline, user)=Before any scoring, fix five things write them down. Locking definitions first what prevents rigged score: **The goal.** one metric Impact serves (e.g., quarterly activations). item's Impact impact goal, Impact column compares apples oranges. **The Reach time window data source.** One window items (e.g., quarter), source named (analytics, CRM, estimate). window set per-item makes ranking meaningless. **The Impact scale.** fixed multipliers: massive, high, medium, 0.5 low, 0.25 minimal. Anchor what means goal scorer reads "2" way. **The Confidence levels.** 100% solid data, 80% data, 50% moonshot; below 50% means validate, score. Agree bias check applied, skipped. **The Effort unit.** Person-months person-weeks, whole-team number. Fix unit denominator currency. Drop any item fails hard gate (no longer scope, blocked, already committed) now, rather scoring it. · h2:Stage Score items (PARALLEL)=Dispatch one scorer subagent initiative, once, given full calibration plus one item. scorers see other, estimates absolute, calibrated scales rather relative others. **Shared framing (send scorer):** Estimate four RICE factors one initiative, against goal: **[GOAL]**. Use exactly calibrated definitions: **[Reach window source, Impact multiplier scale, Confidence levels, Effort unit]**. Initiative: **[INITIATIVE]**. factor give value one-line rationale naming evidence stated assumption behind it. data thin, lower Confidence rather inventing figure; Confidence fall below 50%, say recommend validation instead scoring. return: **Reach**: number, window, source assumption **Impact**: multiplier level **Confidence**: percentage what evidence supports undercuts **Effort**: whole-team estimate fixed unit, what covers **Biggest uncertainty**: factor likely wrong, which way Context: [CONTEXT] Collect items before continuing. Re-dispatch any scorer fails rather synthesizing gap. · h2:Stage Synthesis (SEQUENTIAL, needs items)=One agent assembles ranked roadmap: **Reconcile consistency.** parallel scorers see other, check Reach uses one window, Impact one goal, Effort one unit across item. Adjust any factor estimated off-scale note adjustment. **Compute rank.** item compute (Reach Impact Confidence) Effort, order items score, highest first. **Run sensitivity check.** Vary Confidence Effort (the two swing ranking most) within item's plausible range, re-rank. Report whether order holds (robust) shuffles (fragile), especially among top items sequencing actually bites. **Flag validate-before-committing items.** Any high-rank item resting low Confidence bet, plan: mark "validate before committing" name cheapest test raise Confidence. **Recommend roadmap order, caveats.** Give sequence tied goal horizon, note near-tie means order judgment call, state score informs sequence rather dictating it. · h2:Report structure=Write thorough markdown report save `rice-prioritization-<backlog-slug>-<YYYY-MM-DD>.md` (today's date) working directory unless user names another location. **Header.** goal, planning horizon, date, one-line note framework. State calibration front (Reach window source, Impact scale, Confidence levels, Effort unit) since ranking good these. **Verdict.** recommended roadmap order sentences, whether top list robust close call. **The RICE table.** One row initiative columns Reach, Impact, Confidence, Effort, computed score, rank, sorted score. Scannable glance. **Per-item detail.** initiative: score rank, rationale behind factor, biggest uncertainty, whether flagged validate-before-committing. **Sensitivity note.** ranking moves Confidence Effort vary, which items fragile, which sequencing decisions robust enough commit to. **Recommendation.** roadmap sequence tied goal horizon, items validate first, what new data re-order list. **Caveats.** input estimate, measurement; score rate rewards cheap wins starve large bets still worth making; Confidence guards against wishful thinking cannot manufacture evidence; underestimated Effort silently inflates score; near-ties score ties sequence, mandate; strategic commitment dependency legitimately override higher RICE score. · pr=**Never skip Confidence.** penalizes estimates lack evidence; drop RICE reverts loudest-voice ranking replaced. Below 50%, validate rather score., **Estimate Effort honestly.** denominator, low estimate inflates score most. Estimate committing work, pitching it., **The score sequences, decide.** Strategy, dependencies, missing factor override order.